ermented blended and finished in the west bank occupied territory” could not be labeled “product of israel” in a letter detailing the new labeling policy the board said the government food inspection agency had singled out psagot winery and shiloh winery located in the northern west bank the owners of those wineries expressed shock at the decision which they said would be a major blow to their businesses they said  to  percent of their wine was exported and canada was a major market still they said under no circumstances would they remove israel labeling from their bottles amichai lourie the ceo of shiloh winery located near the major israeli settlement and university town ariel said doing so would be equivalent to carving “traitor” into his forehead “there is no bribe there is no way it would happen that i would take off the wine we make in shiloh winery the words ‘made in israel’” he told jta thursday “it’s the most ungrateful thing that a person could do to make a product in israel and not stand behind it and be proud” yaakov berg the ceo of psagot winery situated on a hilltop overlooking the de facto palestinian capital ramallah said canada’s decision would do symbolic as well as financial harm to west bank settlement wineries like his “canada is important not only because of the market but also because of the image canada is north america it’s not some country in the far east” he told jta thursday “canada used to be our best ally if it happens there who knows what’s next” settlement wineries have boomed in the west bank in the past decade or so according to a  report settlements in the territory are home to  of the more than  wineries in israel and the other territories it captured in the  sixday war compared to  in the famed golan heights wine country several west bank settlement winery owners reported exponential increases in production since the early s much of the world does not recognize israel’s claims to the territories it considers israeli settlements in the territories illegal and in the case of the west bank an impediment to the creation of a palestinian state israel disputes this and has its own complex and evolving laws regarding what makes a settlement legal ontario’s liquor control board the province’s main retailer and distributor of alcohol said the labeling policy applied not just to the west bank but also to “any other territory occupied by israel in ” and named the golan heights eastern jerusalem and the gaza strip because the “government of canada does not recognize israel’s sovereignty over the territories” it said “wine products from these regions that are labeled as ‘product of israel’ would not be acceptable and would be considered misleading” yaakov berg posing at his psagot winery in psagot west bank june   andrew tobin “we are currently seeking clarifications from the cfia on how such wines should be labeled in order to comply with the food and drugs act” the board added canadian food inspection agency did not immediately respond to jta’s interview request in a statement wednesday the jewish advocacy group b’nai brith canada came out against what it called the canadian food inspection agency’s “disturbing decision” it said it expected the agency “will soon rescind its recent decision to order the removal of certain israeli wines from store shelves” meanwhile canaan khoury whose family owns the taybeh winery a palestinian enterprise located between psagot and shiloh welcomed canada’s decision saying it was hard to argue with the logic “it’s not a very surprising decision for a government to try to not be hypocritical” he told jta thursday “if a country recognizes that this location is not israel then why would it accept products being made here being labeled as if they were” taybeh winery is in talks with distributors in canada about exporting to the country but khoury said he did not know what the state’s labeling requirements would be he said his family refuses to label their wines as made in israel which has created bureaucratic hurdles to exporting to some countries canaan khoury posing in a promotional photo at his taybeh winery in the west bank courtesy of taybeh winery like the united states canada does not recognize a palestinian state arguing that it should be established through negotiations between israel and the palestinian authority this is not the first time west bank settler wineries have been involved in a labeling controversy in  the european union issued new guidelines that called on its  member states to label products made by israelis in the west bank as “made in settlements” in addition to wine such labels were to go on fruits and vegetables olive oil honey eggs poultry and cosmetics eu officials downplayed the move as a technical effort meant to ensure clarity about the products’ place of origin but israel reacted angrily and many saw it as an effort to pressure israel over its settlement movement only france has so far implemented the guidelines lourie said the bigger obstacle to selling wines in european countries is the boycott divestment and sanctions movement although west bank wines are recognized for their quality having won accolades at international competitions he said many distributors and vendors do not want the headache of dealing with potential protests he expressed optimism that the situation would be different in canada where he said most people support israel “the impression i get is that the problem in europe is not going to get better it’s going to get worse” he said “in canada i think the situation is different we have many friends there that’s why i didn’t see this coming” berg agreed but in the meantime he said psagot is preparing to sue canada for discrimination related articlesmore from author israel new security cameras at temple mount will respect public and its privacy israel muslim worshippers stay away from temple mount despite removal of metal detectors israel  israelis said killed  wounded in west bank stabbing attack comment take action now follow usfanslikefollowersfollowfollowersfollow subscribe to our newsletter now editor picks tchaikovsky’s jewish problem culture july   adl condemns sermons by california imams that called for destruction of religion july   how tisha b’av can help us understand the refugee experience middle east july   popular posts  jewish inventions that changed the world blog february    jewish inventions that changed the world blog july   jspace quotables  memorable quotes about the holocaust blog january   popular categorycurrent eventsisraelunited statesblogworldeuropepoliticsentertainmentjudaism about usjspace news is one of the fastest growing online jewish newspapers founded in  to document news on israel the middle east and jewish world at large it was established to provide a single source where the entire jewish and israeli community could come together in conversationfollow us about advertise with us terms and conditions privacy policy help find us on google  copyright   jewish world alliance all rights reserved wowmodalwindows id israel archives  jspace news current events israel middle east united states europe world politics judaism religion history innovation education environment health science  technology culture art style travel organizations dating food entertainment gossip music sports business finance legal search wednesday july   jspace food contact us donate sign in welcome log into your account your username your password forgot your password get help password recovery recover your password your email a password will be emailed to you jspace news current events israel middle east united states europe world politics judaism religion history innovation education environment health science  technology culture art style travel organizations dating food entertainment gossip music sports business finance legal home israel israel latest latestfeatured postsmost popular days popularby review scorerandom new security cameras at